		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Without the nub its normal for the system to think some direction is pressed. The nub is 2x potentiometers in single casing, and the position of the nub is determined by the resistance on the pots, no pots = certain resistance seen by the machine which translates to some certain direction.
<br />
<br />Clean the nub up, perhaps even bend its brushes a bit and reassemble and hope for the best

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

