	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Now we know why Nintendo's <a href="http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TonkaTough" class="postlink">Tonka-tough reputation</a> took a hit once its products started incorporating moving parts such as analog sticks, optical disc drives, and flip-up screens. The first thing to go on a GameCube controller, for example, is the left analog stick. And on a DS Lite, the L and R buttons are the first thing to go, and I'm pretty sure their design was a compromise due to the requirement of a flip-up screen.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
